subsection.p:
The gradient is the vector that represents this same measurement when we use the
Euclidean dot product:
\boxed{df_{\mathbf p}(\mathbf v) = \nabla f(\mathbf p)\cdot \mathbf v.}

Its flux form is
\boxed{\Phi_{\mathbf F} = P\,dy\wedge dz + Q\,dz\wedge dx + R\,dx\wedge dy.}
This is integrated over surfaces.

